I'm a level 52 mage. I like my mage and after playing lots of other classes (granted... not to a very high level) my Mage is my favorite. <P>I have but one request for a change really. (I could cite other requests, but they all seem to pale in comparison to this one..)<P>Without nerfing our pets, remove the requirement that we must outdamage them in order to get full exp for a kill. we have no root, we have no snare, we have no real means of escape (other than our pets... which I'm getting to..). The reasoning is simply this:<P>My pet is both my armor and my weapon. I live and die by my pet. If I summon a sword and melee something do I have to outdamage the sword in order to get exp? Does a warrior have to somehow outdamage his weapon to get exp? Without my pet I am NOT an efficient damage dealer (I'm talking primarily solo here since that's where the damage penalty actually comes into play.) Remove the damage penalty and I do NOT think we've unbalanced anything. <P>Perilbane Mooncaster<BR>Mage of the 52nd Circle<P>PS... oh yeah... and why the hell did I put all that effort into research only to find that after 50 I can't research ANY of my spells?<P>
