Every class has its drawbacks. Some classes are worse than others. Mages drawbacks are minimal. Most people who are complaining about the class seem to just not know how to play a mage correctly. Are there some minor tweaks that could help the mage class? Yes. However, you can't take away reasonable disadvantages from the class and still have playing the character fun.<P>Someone falls off a bridge and dies - uh, lev ring would have solved that problem.<P>We don't get SoW - uh, camp jboots.<P>We get invis so most mobs won't see us when we travel. Before I got my giant faction up I ran through Kael invis so I would not agro. I did not have to worry like clerics and warriors that sit at the zone waiting for someone to come by and invis them so they can travel through.<P>Yes, it would be nice to have more summons. However, I use mod rods, lev rings, and coldstones on a daily basis. There are situations where sword of runes, dispel staffs, MR/PR/DR daggers, and waterstones are needed. CoH summons other players. Pets are summoned. Yes, half our summons are worthless, but the ones we have that are not worthless are worth a hell of a lot more than toilet paper. Somehow I think you would complain bitterly if they took away the good ones that you already have.<P>Oh, and speaking of pets...that is how Mages kill MOBs. Our nukes are OK, but are not our primary form of damage. I can solo mobs just dandy when I want to. And using the correct pet in the correct situation in a group makes it so that you can do things with a group that you normally couldn't.<P>Obviously you have no clue how to use AEs, or you would not call them useless.<P>Obviously you do not know how play a mage well. Obviously you have never played a crappy class or you would realize how great Mages are.<P>Tepid<BR>Level 56 Mage<BR>Mith Marr<P>
