<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Well.... The only ONE thing that i think mages need (and i know many that will agree with me) is Group friendly ...anythings.<P>   Pets are not group friendly, UNLESS, you can control your pets, but this is a tough task indeed for how much our pets our worth in Kunark situations and especially velious.<P>Example:<P>Sebilis Juggernaut Raid:  im a 55 magician, was asked to join a 2 group juggernaut raid (going all the way past the reet knights into Trakanon's room).  Tell me, why do you think they asked me to join the raid?.. for Damage dealing?.. for my "awsome BALANCED" pets?.. no.. it was for CoH.  They knew that, and i knew that.  This is our only real group friendly spell in Kunark/velious.. its an amazing spell, dont get me wrong, but its the only thing anyone thinks of when they think of 55 + magicians.. not the pets.. not the DDs.<P>   As many of you may know.. to get to the Juggs, you have to be constantly on the move, killing level 53+ Mobs left and right, and a lot of times getting multiples, and once you get multiples, you alwasy have Enchanters Mezzing/rooting.  <P>Mage, stands around, dmg shielding tanks.. has no pet because he was on the move and pathing dis allows the use of pets. not only pathing but the fact the pets will break mezzed mobs as well, and this can be a life or death situation if it happens.  So the little that we have left, which i actually found useful, is Malosi.  I always was casting Malosi on every Shroom that we pulled to make it much easier for the Enchanters to mez.  This is funny because before 50.. we did all the Damage (A lot of it done by the pets), now im just helping the enchanters mez mobs so that the tanks can do all the damage.<P>   Our role in these situations has changed completely.  i dont think i had casted one nuke on any mob on the way down to Traks lair.. not one.  Its pretty ridiculous to waste 175, or 399 mana to cast Scars of sigil or sirocco (which is highly resisted.. especially against 53 + mobs wtf its almost useless unless you solo mobs that are under 50.. then it usually works great) and 450 dmg is next to nothing compared to what both groups are doing.. especially the Warriors and monks.. <P>   level 59 monk outdamaged my entire group, we had a mage pet, necro pet, a wizard and i think a shaman.. ... we were all casting like mad as well, (also hard nuking at the end in case there still is the hate dmg list.) And the monk still got some of the kills.. <P>(sorry if im confusing, i tend to ramble in no particular order)<P>   Anyways.. to sum up what ive had to say, <P>1) We need to be more Group friendly.. i dont care How you do it (verant) just do it.. i like to group, hard to find a group for anything else but CoH. *shrug*<P>2) Maybe post 55, our pets should doing a lot more dmg than you have set them?, i know this would cause an unbalance in Pre-kunark/velious dungeons, but i dont think it would hurt.  Especially since we now would want to group in the new dungeons, our pets MIGHT be a little more effective.  Or maybe give us a new spell line that will make us more group friendly, that makes us a necessity other than CoH (see how i stress this). some kind of lure?... (i know i know, stepping on wizards toes).. or make our AoE Rain spells a LOT less resisted.. so we can actually deal some real damage.. even with sirocco (max dmg 1890, which is an AWSOME, dmg / mana ratio) on these new mobs we are just dealing nothing ( 100k hps.. 2000 hps isnt going to do much).. and take into consideration that we DO run out of mana, and on these new mobs we are useless.. once we run out of mana, we are utterly completely useless, but to stand around and maybe Tank a melee round to save a Warrior, or someone much more needed.<P>3) pet control.. i like the /pet no attack idea.. do it.  (although i already dont have much problems with handling my pets, it is an annoyance to me when my pet switches targets or beats on mezzed mobs every once in a while.) <P><BR>Deminn Rhys (used to be Nass but offended the GMs *sigh*)<BR>55 Conjurer<BR>Tarew Marr<P><BR>
</FONT>
