I am really wondering about the disgrunteled old mage here.  The only (somewhat) relevent point I think he has is about the usefulness of our summoned items.  Other than that, I would only agree with the fact that our 50+ pets suck hard.  Granted, I am only level 25 and don't play as often as I would like to, I have heard from more than just 40 mages that the problems originally posted were not the problems to be addressing.  Correct me if I'm wrong but the Earth pets are modeled after warriors, water after rouge, air after monk, and fire after wizard right.  The only thing good about these pets that I've heard is that the water pet can backstab.  Well, thats great for the water pet!  I want to know how much earth pets attack for and get hit for, I want to know how much overall damage output an air pet has, I want to know how good the fire pets blast is (it IS modeled after a wizard afterall).  From what I hear most mages complain about, these are the major problems with our class.  I just hope they make the class desireable post 50 by the time I get there.
